'''Foreword to ''A New Glossary of the Dialect of the Huddersfield District''''' refers to [[J.R.R. Tolkien]]'s Foreword to ''[[A New Glossary of the Dialect of the Huddersfield District]]'' ([[1928]]) by Walter E. Haigh.

In his Foreword, Tolkien discusses the compilation of glossaries and the development of the English language in [[Wikipedia:Northern England|Northern England]].<ref name=TB>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://www.tolkienbooks.net/php/details.php?reference=13340|articlename=New Glossary of the Dialect of the Huddersfield District. 1928|dated=|website=TB|accessed=1 January 2012}}</ref>

